Toyota sets the total amount of remuneration received by each director in a year based on consolidated operating income, the volatility of the share price of Toyota and individual performance evaluation [1]. The determination of remuneration considers corporate performance, individual job responsibilities, and performance, aligning with the remuneration policy established by the Board of Directors [10].

 &nbsp; 

 The "Annual Total Remuneration" is determined based on the benchmark results of executive compensation, considering both consolidated operating income and the volatility of Toyota's share price, with adjustments made based on individual performance evaluation [11].

 &nbsp; 

 The consolidated operating income indicates Toyota’s efforts based on business performance and volatility of Toyota’s share price indicates corporate value for shareholders and investors to evaluate Toyota’s efforts based on these metrics.  ![Consolidated operating income and share price volatility are key indicators in executive compensation.](image5)

 &nbsp; 

Toyota's executive remuneration evaluation reflects business performance through consolidated operating income and shareholder value indicators like the volatility of Toyota's share price [1, 11, 5].
